text: James Edward Proctor, Jr. (June 14, 1936 - September 10, 2015) was an American politician. He represented district 27A in the Maryland House of Delegates from May 1990 until his death. Proctor was born in Washington, D.C. to an African American family. He lived in Accokeek, Maryland with his wife Elizabeth G. Proctor.
